        <abstract> 
<p>Sends seeds of <hi rend="italic">Lathyrus</hi> and suggests an advantage of climbing plants is to shed their seeds in places secure from animals.</p>  
<p>Contrary to F. Delpino, in JTM’s experience <hi rend="italic">Ophrys aranifera</hi> is not sterile. However, seed germination is poor.</p>  
<p>In a densely overgrown plot <hi rend="italic">Convolvulus sabatius</hi>, not normally a twiner, becomes one.</p>  
<p>Continues his extensive study on variability in <hi rend="italic">Arbutus</hi>, and speculates on selection in fruit shape.</p> 
        </abstract>
